main event: Several unidentified objects were reported in flight over Lubbock, Texas on August 30, 1951.
interesting points: The objects were visible in a night sky and were depicted as a series of small points of light in a curved formation., The images included were part of the Project Blue Book document on unidentified aerial phenomena., One photograph appeared as a negative showing bright streaks or trails of light., The objects were hard to distinguish clearly due to graininess in the photographs., The sightings were officially documented as part of a U.S. Air Force investigation.
sighted object: unidentified objects in flight, described as points of light
